[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     12[0m:[38;5;10m[49m No ERROR-level findings. Two WARNING-level findings (under the FAIL threshold of >3). Several NOTE-level improvements. The DynamoDB Decimal discipline is consistent across every `put_item` site, the S3 keys are unprefixed, the boto3 SDK calls (Bedrock Knowledge Base `retrieve`, Connect `start_chat_contact`, EventBridge `put_events`, Step Functions `start_execution`, S3 `put_object` with KMS) match the current API surface, and the demo wires together a coherent end-to-end recruitment-conversation pipeline. The two warnings concern (1) a disposition-value bug where `prescreen_state` is reused as a decision-record `disposition` field, producing records with non-taxonomic codes, and (2) the agent loop dropping intermediate text blocks issued alongside `tool_use` content, which means the first-turn IRB-required disclosures scripted into the demo never actually reach the user.
