[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     33[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The vulnerable-populations identity model is realized through the IDENTITY_* taxonomy and the `identity_posture` check in `receive_conversation_turn`. Per-trial isolation is enforced through `trial_id` partition keys on every store, the `trial_id` filter on the FAQ Knowledge Base retrieval, and the post-hoc `trial_id` check in `tool_recruitment_faq_retrieve`. The deterministic-eligibility-evaluation discipline is realized through `evaluate_eligibility_criterion` and the four CRITERION_CATEGORY_* tags. The IRB-amendment workflow is sketched (the Step Functions ARN is a placeholder and the full re-presentation flow is described in prose only), which the recipe acknowledges in the gap-to-production section.
