[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Once `funnel_stage` flips to `FUNNEL_STAGE_HANDOFF_SCHEDULED` (in `tool_coordinator_handoff_request`), every subsequent turn re-runs this block and writes another decision record. Each new record has a fresh `decision_id`, a new `_now_iso()` `ended_at`, and a re-built `prescreen_summary`. The S3 bucket and the DynamoDB decision-record table accumulate duplicate records keyed by different `decision_id`s for the same `session_id`.
